clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For use in the induction and maintenance of general anesthesia

contraindications.disease: LD sub 50 sub 3600 mg kg Orally in rats Symptoms of overexposure include eye irritation CNS depression analgesia anesthesia seizures respiratory depression and liver and kidney damage
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Methoxyflurane is a general inhalation anesthetic used for induction and maintenance of general anesthesia It induces muscle relaxation and reduces pains sensitivity by altering tissue excitability It does so by decreasing the extent of gap junction mediated cell cell coupling and altering the activity of the channels that underlie the action potential
